{{See|Mistress}}
==English==
=== Etymology ===
From Middle English ''[[maistresse]]'', from earlier Old French, feminine of ''[[maistre]]'', master

===Pronunciation===
*mĭsʹtrĭs, /ˈmɪstrɪs/, /<tt>"mIstrIs</tt>/

=== Noun ===
{{WikiSaurus-link}}
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun-reg-es}}

# a woman, specifically one with control, [[authority]] or ownership
#:''She was the mistress of the mansion, and owned the horses.''
# a female teacher
#:''games mistress''
# a woman who ([[dishonorably]]) [[displace]]s a wife in the affections of a man; a woman, other than his wife, with whom a married man has a continuing sexual relationship
# a [[dominatrix]]

